x4freetext: Typical Time Interval Between End of Irradiation and
End of Chemical Separation was 20 Min.
The Target Consisted of Three U-Foils, Thickness
134 Mg/Cm**2, Carefully Aligned, the Two Outer Foils
Serving to Compensate For Recoil Losses and of Two
Cu-Foils, Thickness 44 Mg/Cm**2, Placed Upstream of
The U-Foils. The Outer Cu-Foil Served As a Monitor
Foil. The Whole Stack was Wrapped in Thin Al-Foil.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The Errors Quoted are the Total Errors
Including Uncertainties of Monitor Cross Sections
(5.4%), Detector Efficiencies (1%), Chemical Yield
(4%), and Target Superficial Density (2%).
An Additional Error Due to Counting Statistics was
Added For Each Individual Determination.  In Most
Measurements It Rarely Exceeds 2%.  Not Included were
Errors Due to Decay Schemes and Half-Lives.
The Uncertainty in Beam Energy was +-2 MeV.
Shielded
The Cu-Monitor Foils were Chemically Treated, Too, to
Remove All Non-Cu Contaminants.
